# Local MCP config — contains credentials, never commit
.mcp.json

# Claude Code local settings — contains POE_SESSION_ID in permission command
# strings, never commit. Shareable .claude content (skills/, agents/, commands/,
# settings.json) IS tracked; only the .local file is ignored.
.claude/settings.local.json

# Per-character analysis notes — kept local, may reference character names/build details.
# The directory itself is a junction (Windows) / symlink (Unix) into an external dir
# (%APPDATA%/poe_claude_data on Windows). The real data lives outside the repo so it
# survives `rm -rf` of the suite and can be backed up / transferred independently.
# See character_data/README.md (i.e. the README inside the junction target) for the layout.
character_data

# Cached game knowledge from wiki/external sources — kept local for fast lookup, regenerable.
# Ignore the cached data itself but keep the README so future setup instructions are preserved.
# Skilltree and atlas tree forks are tracked as submodules (the PATCHES.md protocol doc lives
# inside each fork, traveling with the data it documents).
reference_data/*
!reference_data/README.md
!reference_data/skilltree
!reference_data/atlastree
# Curated model-aware index of post-training mechanics — committed (travels with the suite,
# referenced by the freshness-check skill), unlike the regenerable cached data alongside it.
!reference_data/freshness_index.md
# Curated index of external build-guide aggregators (discovery resources) — committed, useful to
# every clone (parallels freshness_index.md), unlike the per-character digested guides in the cache.
!reference_data/guide_sources.md
# Curated index of patch-note / hotfix thread links — committed, the authoritative "what changed"
# diff that pairs with freshness_index.md. Useful to every clone.
!reference_data/patch_notes_index.md
# Mechanic-keyed registry with scope tags (core / challenge-league / event-only / removed / disabled) —
# committed; the compartmentalization layer that keeps league/event data from bleeding into the wrong build.
!reference_data/mechanics_index.md

# Local game-data extraction scratch space.
# See legal_considerations.md — most output from pathofexile-dat / bundle extraction is
# "extract at runtime, never republish" content (stat description templates, AlternatePassive
# tables, mod pools, etc.). Keep these strictly local.
data-extraction-poc/
data-extraction-cache/
*.bundle.bin
*.datc64
poe-schema.json
